   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Machine Translation Evaluator\\n\",\"**NLP Project 61 of 100** — Compare translation quality across models and language pairs using BLEU and human evaluation.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\nfor pkg in ['pandas','numpy','matplotlib','seaborn','sacrebleu','transformers','torch']:\\n    try: importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,'-m','pip','install','-q',pkg])\\nprint('Ready.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, pandas as pd, matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\nimport sacrebleu\\nfrom transformers import pipeline\\nimport torch\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nsns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n%matplotlib inline\\ndevice = 0 if torch.cuda.is_available() else -1\\nprint(f'Device: {\\\"GPU\\\" if device==0 else \\\"CPU\\\"}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# Test sentences (English → French)\\nsources = ['The cat sat on the mat.','Machine learning is changing the world.','I love reading books about science.']\\nreferences = ['Le chat était assis sur le tapis.','L\\\\'apprentissage automatique change le monde.','J\\\\'adore lire des livres sur la science.']\\n\\n# Translate with Helsinki-NLP model\\ntranslator = pipeline('translation', model='Helsinki-NLP/opus-mt-en-fr', device=device)\\ntranslations = [translator(s)[0]['translation_text'] for s in sources]\\n\\nfor s, r, t in zip(sources, references, translations):\\n    print(f'EN: {s}')\\n    print(f'Reference: {r}')\\n    print(f'Model:     {t}\\\\n')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# BLEU score\\nbleu = sacrebleu.corpus_bleu(translations, [references])\\nprint(f'BLEU Score: {bleu.score:.1f}')\\n\\n# Per-sentence BLEU\\nfor i, (t, r) in enumerate(zip(translations, references)):\\n    sent_bleu = sacrebleu.sentence_bleu(t, [r])\\n    print(f'  Sentence {i+1} BLEU: {sent_bleu.score:.1f}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **BLEU measures n-gram overlap** between translation and reference.\\n\",\"- **Scores above 30 indicate reasonable quality**; above 50 is good.\\n\",\"- **BLEU has limitations**: it misses semantic equivalence and penalizes valid paraphrases.\\n\",\"- **For production, combine BLEU with COMET** or human evaluation.\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
